To generate a table of contents (TOC) in a LATEX document, you can use the `\tableofcontents` command. You also need to use the `\addcontentsline` command to add the chapters and sections to the TOC.

Here's an example:

```latex
\documentclass{book}
\begin{document}
\tableofcontents

\part{Part One}
\chapter{Chapter One}
\label{ch:one}
\addcontentsline{toc}{chapter}{\protect\numberline{}Chapter One}

\section{Section One}
\label{sec:one}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{\protect\numberline{\thechapter.\thesection}Section One}

\section{Section Two}
\label{sec:two}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{\protect\numberline{\thechapter.\thesection}Section Two}

\chapter{Chapter Two}
\label{ch:two}
